Salary: Our people build skills for the future
Ad Text:
Job Description

Enterprise Advisory provides business transformation, risk & assurance, and technology outcomes to mid-market clients through the delivery of consulting, internal audit and implementation services. Our purpose is to unlock tangible value for our clients, shoulder to shoulder, from strategy through to execution, enabled by technology and deep operational expertise to facilitate, growth, efficiency, resilience and sustainability.

Your Opportunity

We currently have exciting opportunities for Managers, Associate Directors and Directors, across our Enterprise Advisory division.

Risk and Assurance

Our Risk team design and transform risk functions, create, and build enterprise risk management frameworks, advise on Governance, risk and controls solutions and support businesses in identifying and managing operational risks. Risk Consulting is a growing business that focuses on helping our clients understand, manage, and oversee their risks, including conduct and regulatory change. 

Business Transformation

Our purpose is to unlock tangible value for our clients from strategy to execution, enabled by technology and deep operational expertise. Within this team, our Business Transformation division is involved in both shaping and operationalising business strategies, as well as designing and managing projects and client delivery.

Technology Advisory

Our Enterprise Technology Advisory team brings together skills in intelligent automation, data engineering and software integration to help our clients align their technology capabilities with their strategic and operational objectives. We also draw on KPMG’s extensive national and global resources, adopting a multidisciplinary approach to help unlock the full potential of existing and new technology investments.

How are you extraordinary?

You have a can-do attitude and are always seeking creative solutions to problems with the help of the right technical tools and a supportive team

You are tuned in to business development opportunities, with confidence creating effective sales material including proposals, case studies, and other sector-specific material

You are passionate about the importance of fantastic communication to share ideas, inspire, and create change. You are able to digest, distil, and communicate complex concepts in both written and verbal forms

You are a project management pro, with a love of big-picture thinking and the skills to see projects from beginning to end; such as establishing project details, performance measurement baselines, key milestones, work breakdown structures, and resource planning.

Your Experience

At KPMG, we believe diversity of thought, background and experience strengthens relationships and delivers meaningful benefits to our people, our clients, and communities. To be considered for this opportunity, your qualifications, skills & experience could include:

Risk and Assurance

Relevant post-graduate professional qualifications such as risk management, information technology, project management, data analysis, engineering, law, process improvement, commerce, CA, CPA or CIA

Strong Risk Consulting, Internal Audit, Process Improvement, Business Analyst, Data Analysis, Project Management, Operational or External Audit experience in a professional services firm or industry

Highly developed report writing, communication and presentation skills desirable.

Business Transformation

Experience or exposure to the practical application of continuous improvement methodologies such as Agile, Lean or Six Sigma

Experience in Management Consulting is highly desirable, or an ability to demonstrate background in internal facing consulting services

Experience working with FMCG/Food and Beverage sector highly regarded (not essential)

Highly developed ability to translate business and customer needs into best practice process and operation design requirements

Understanding or exposure to business and / or technology solution design and target operating model design and delivery.

Technology Advisory

Previous 5 + years’ experience working for a well-regarded Management Consulting firm

Experience or exposure to the practical application of continuous improvement cycles

Strong understanding of process architecture and process design, with an ability to link business processes to technology requirements

Strong understanding of how to execute on the following, with guidance and supervision of senior SMEs:

Apply best practice frameworks in operations and technology

Research market and industry data, with a second to none ability to be a data driven thinker, comfortable with analysing large volumes of qualitative and quantitative data and information to inform IT strategies

Define IT strategies, designing technology architectures and technology operating models, and developing technology roadmaps, all of them with a business-led approach using best practice frameworks

Shape IT strategy execution and IT transformation roadmaps that go beyond paper

Embed technology into the design and implementation of business operating models

Build a business case for business and technology investments

Structured problem solving with capability to canvas the path to a part of a solution.

Technology Enablement

Previous experience working for a well-regarded Management Consulting firm focused on Oracle Implementations will be highly regarded

Demonstrated experience implementing ERP solutions including Oracle Cloud ERP solutions, preferably with ability to demonstrate strong GL experience

Experience working across other pillars such as SCM and HCM or as a techno-functional consultant will be highly regarded

Application and Solution architecture experience from a functional perspective is highly desirable

Ability to work with a broad range of technology solutions that are commonly integrated with ERP solutions, and approaches to technology governance and project management skills

Undergraduate technology, accounting or finance-based degree and 5+ years’ work experience.

Please note, the salary ranges $110 – $200K+ with respect to your level of experience.

We are hiring for the following employment types: Casual, Max-Term Full-Time, Max-Term Part-Time, Permanent Full-Time & Permanent Part-Time.

We have offices in the following locations:

Sydney

Melbourne

Brisbane

Perth

Canberra

Adelaide

Hobart

Gold Coast

Darwin

Townsville

Parramatta

Wollongong

Newcastle/Hunter Region

Geelong

Qualifications

Specific qualifications are mentioned above

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Senior Data & Reporting Analyst (6-Month Contract) - Critical Utility Asset Optimisation

The Opportunity & Details

An exciting 6-month contract opportunity has arisen for a highly skilled Senior Data and Reporting Analyst to join a critical Asset Management Optimisation Project within a complex, regulated utility environment.

Contract Rate: $1,000.00 - $1,100.00 per day (Inclusive of Superannuation)

Contract Duration: 6 months, with a strong likelihood of extension based on project needs and performance.

Location: Home-based / Flexible, with compulsory interstate travel to a dedicated operational location one week per month for the duration (all travel and accommodation expenses covered).

This is a high-impact role where your expertise in data analysis, visualisation, and reporting will directly drive strategic and operational decisions in a sector where reliability and compliance are paramount.

Your Responsibilities

As the Senior Data and Reporting Analyst, you will be crucial in translating complex data into actionable business intelligence, both remotely and on-site:

Data Strategy & Quality: Lead the collection, quality assurance, cleansing, and integration of complex data streams from multiple platforms (including asset management systems) specific to a utility or heavily regulated environment.

BI Development: Design, develop, and administer strategic and tactical reports, dashboards, and advanced visualisation/alerting mechanisms using Tableau Desktop and Server.

Technical Expertise: Write and optimize complex queries using Oracle SQL to support data extraction, performance tuning, and integrity across the reporting environment.

Stakeholder Engagement: Proactively liaise with business unit stakeholders to gather requirements, analyse and improve processes, and deliver data-driven insights.

Process Improvement: Identify and implement opportunities for continuous improvement, process automation, and the integration of paper-based forms into digital workflows.

Essential Skills and Experience

To be successful in this contract, you must demonstrate:

Critical Industry Experience: Demonstrated and recent experience working in a complex, regulated multi-utility environment (e.g., Water, Power, Gas, or similar heavy infrastructure) is critical.

Travel Readiness: Unrestricted ability and willingness to travel interstate to a dedicated operational site for one week per month for the entire 6-month contract duration.

Proven Seniority: Extensive experience in data cleansing, manipulating complex datasets, and ensuring data integrity in dynamic, large-scale environments.

Tableau Expert: Essential proficiency in Tableau Desktop for creating interactive dashboards and reports, and experience with Tableau Server for publishing and managing performance.

SQL Mastery: Strong expertise in Oracle SQL for writing complex queries, advanced joins, and performance tuning.

Highly Desirable Assets

Familiarity with Power BI (including data modelling and DAX) or a strong willingness to cross-skill.

Prior experience working with IBM Maximo or similar Asset Management systems for data extraction and integration.

Apply Now

If you are a resourceful, high-performing Senior Analyst with critical utility sector experience and are fully prepared for the compulsory monthly interstate travel, we encourage you to apply today for this excellent contract opportunity with a competitive daily rate and strong possibility of extension!


Please contact Joseph Demetriou () for a confidential discussion about the role.

Salary: Our people build skills for the future
Ad Text:
Company Description

Want to help shape the future of learning at KPMG? At KPMG, we believe that our people are at the heart of everything we do. Join our People & Inclusion team as the Head of Learning and play a pivotal role in delivering business strategy, shaping our culture, and empowering our people to thrive.

KPMG is proud to have launched the KPMG Learning Academy- a key enabler of our culture transformation, designed to continuously build and develop the capability of our people, empowering them to thrive and adapt in a rapidly changing world.

Job Description

As the Head of Learning, you will lead the firm's learning and development strategy, ensuring it is aligned with KPMG’s values, purpose, and strategic priorities. You will oversee the KPMG Learning Academy and its innovative portfolio, including firmwide, divisional, and mandatory learning programs. This role is also a mix of strategic leadership, creative design, and team management, where you will:

Collaborate with senior stakeholders across divisions to design and deploy high-impact, market-leading learning solutions tailored to business needs.

Lead the development and execution of the firm’s 3-year learning strategy, including future-skilling our people in areas such as ESG, Digital, AI, and Data.

Oversee the design and deployment of firmwide onboarding, graduate programs, mandatory learning, and continuous professional development.

Transform learning into a scalable, innovative, and learner-centred experience through data-driven insights, the latest learning technologies, and contemporary development practises.

Build and develop a high-performing team of learning managers and consultants.

Represent Australia in global and regional learning initiatives, sharing key insights and contributing to international thought leadership in learning.

Your Opportunity

At KPMG, we’re committed to your growth and creating a vibrant culture. In this high-energy senior leadership role, you’ll collaborate closely with global experts and local leaders across all areas of our firm to drive real impact. You'll enjoy:

Impact and influence: Shape tomorrow's workforce by defining and implementing KPMG’s learning strategies while helping our people and clients stay future-ready.

Innovation: Push creative and traditional design boundaries to develop market-leading learning solutions.

Professional growth: Be part of a dynamic team committed to your personal and professional development.

Diversity and inclusion: Join a workplace that champions diversity, fostering innovation through collaboration and inclusion.

How are you Extraordinary?

You are a purpose-driven, values-led leader who is passionate about delivering large-scale, world-class learning and development solutions. You have a track record of building strong relationships, challenging the status quo, and creating impactful learning experiences. You’ll bring:

Deep experience in leadership and executive development, learning strategy design, and large-scale implementation.

A strong ability to influence and collaborate with senior stakeholders, including leveraging robust consulting skills to interpret organisational needs and deliver tailored solutions.

Demonstrated expertise in creating innovative, scalable, learner-centric solutions using modern design thinking, user experience (UX) design, and advanced learning technologies.

Proven experience in leading and inspiring high-performing teams.

A data-driven mindset, leveraging insights to measure impact and demonstrate ROI.

A passion for future-focused learning and staying at the forefront of trends in areas like workforce transformation, the future of work, and AI in learning.

Exceptional interpersonal, facilitation, and communication skills to deliver results in a complex, matrixed environment.

Join us in shaping the future of learning and unlocking the potential of extraordinary people!

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

About Us

Fortescue is both a proud West Australian company and a global green solutions business. We are recognised for our culture, innovation and industry-leading development of infrastructure, mining assets and green energy initiatives.

Our Opportunity

Work Location: Perth - Fortescue's Perth office is located on the traditional lands of the Whadjuk Noongar people.

Roster: Monday to Friday

We are looking for a Senior Data Engineer to design, build, and optimize scalable data systems using modern cloud and data engineering practices. You will develop robust data architectures and pipelines that provide curated, analytics-ready data for Data Analysts, Data Scientists, and business teams.

This role requires close collaboration with the Analysts, Data Scientists, the Offshore team, and broader business stakeholders to deliver data-driven solutions that enable actionable insights. As a senior member of the team, you will also mentor offshore team members, providing guidance on best practices in technology, coding standards, and solution design.

If you thrive in a fast-paced environment and are passionate about unlocking the value of data, we'd love to hear from you.

Key Responsibilities

Architect, build and optimize scalable data pipelines and provisioning processes, ensuring timely, reliable and production-ready data products
Develop secure, compliant, and governed data storage solutions across cloud platforms and enterprise systems
Create reusable code, libraries and tools to streamline data access, interpretation and transformation
Automate data preparation and integration tasks using metadata-driven approaches and AI-enabled techniques
Monitor schema changes, data usage patterns and implement smart sampling/caching to improve performance
Work extensively with AWS services (Lambda, Step Functions, S3, RDS, EC2) and manage secure, scalable Snowflake environments
Define and maintain Infrastructure-as-Code using AWS CDK, Terraform and automation frameworks
Implement CI/CD pipelines with GitHub Actions, ensuring robust testing, secure deployments and engineering best practices
Collaborate with Data Analysts, Data Scientists, offshore teams and business stakeholders to deliver governed, high-quality data solutions
Produce and maintain documentation on architecture, engineering standards, patterns and best practices
Provide technical leadership through code reviews, mentoring, coaching offshore teams and supporting data profiling, analysis and visualization activities.

Qualifications and Experience

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field, or equivalent practical experience
10+ years' experience in Data Engineering with strong capability in designing, building and optimising scalable data pipeline
Extensive experience with cloud platforms—particularly AWS—and delivering cloud-based data engineering solutions
Strong proficiency in SQL for advanced querying, performance tuning and data modelling
Expert Python skills for data engineering, automation and pipeline development, with additional experience in JavaScript beneficial
Hands-on experience with Snowflake, including administration, optimisation and integration into data pipelines
Strong understanding of data modelling best practices across cloud, hybrid and on-prem environments
Experience with BI and analytics tools (Tableau, Power BI, Spotfire) and knowledge of visualisation best practices
Solid grounding in DevOps/DataOps practices—CI/CD, Git/GitHub, GitHub Actions, and IaC tools such as Terraform and AWS CDK
Strong communication, documentation and problem-solving skills, with experience in Agile delivery frameworks and the ability to mentor and collaborate in cross-functional teams.

Our Commitment

Fortescue is deeply committed to providing a safe culture that builds respect, fosters inclusiveness, and values diversity. We celebrate individual strengths and team members from all backgrounds are encouraged to bring their whole selves to work. Our global workforce drives and promotes an inclusive culture, both within our organisation and throughout the communities we interact with across the world. Diverse backgrounds include First Nations Peoples, people with differing abilities, LGBTIQ+ community, gender, neurodiverse, cultural diversity, all age groups, and those with an intersectional or multiple diverse characteristics. We encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply.

https://fortescue.com/careers

2 x Business Analysts

Contract for 6 months | Brisbane CBD + WFH

We’re partnering with a Queensland Government department to engage two experienced Business Analysts for a key project focused on improving how operational field activities are captured, managed, and reported across the organisation.

This project centres on how field officers currently record operational activities across various tools and formats, and how this information is consolidated into mandatory reporting for the Queensland Government.

These roles will directly contribute to uplifting data capture processes, improving reporting quality, and shaping the future-state solution that will support the department’s operational and legislative requirements.

Develop a comprehensive business case for a future-state operational data capture and reporting system, ensuring alignment with government requirements.

Conduct a detailed analysis of existing data capture tools, assess suitability, identify gaps, and recommend improvements.

Refine or modify current tools to ensure compliance with government data quality and reporting standards.

Engage with operational staff and project stakeholders to gather requirements, map processes, and validate findings.

Support documentation, workshops, and recommendations that guide future system and process changes.

What We’re Looking For:

Proven experience as a Business Analyst within government, regulatory, emergency services, or data-heavy environments.

Strong analytical capability across data capture, reporting, and process improvement.

Ability to translate operational requirements into clear business cases and solution recommendations.

Associate Director – M&A

Melbourne or Sydney | Hybrid | Full-Time | Strategy and M&A Team

Tenet Advisory & Investments is an advisory and investments firm built for a changing world. Founded on the principles of momentum, growth and value creation, we partner with clients to deliver a better today and an even stronger tomorrow.

Our team brings together talented and passionate professionals from diverse disciplines and industries. Working as one collaborative unit, we apply smart business principles to help our clients navigate the complex challenges they face in private, public, government and industry settings.

This is a leadership role within an advisory context, you’ll work across both transaction advisory and strategic engagements, helping clients navigate their commercial and growth‑oriented objectives.

Apply strong financial acumen and commercial judgment, including P&L, balance sheet, cash flow, and working capital analysis, to assess company performance and value relative to peers

Lead strategy and transformation initiatives, including market research, competitor analysis, growth pathways, business cases, synergy and integration planning, and business improvement projects

Lead, coach, and mentor project teams, including Tenet team members, client stakeholders, and external subject matter experts

Engage and influence senior leaders and executives, managing stakeholder expectations and facilitating decision-making

Oversee multiple projects simultaneously, ensuring high-quality output, attention to detail, and alignment with client requirements

About you

6+ years’ experience in M&A, investment banking, corporate development, strategy consulting, private equity, or transaction advisory services.

Experience preparing and presenting high-quality client materials.

Proven ability to work with senior stakeholders.

Commercial judgment, attention to detail, and a hands-on approach.

Relevant tertiary qualification in finance, commerce, economics, or related field.

Why Tenet?

Hybrid working: 4 days in-office, 1 day remote, aligned to client requirements

Competitive remuneration and discretionary bonus

$5,000 annual wellness & development package

25 days annual leave + 5 “Tenet Leave” days

Generous and flexible parental leave offering

Access to EAP (confidential counselling)

Employee Share Option Plan

Opportunity to gain exposure to Strategy projects in an agile, cross-functional team

If you’re excited to be part of a high-impact team shaping the future of Tenet, apply now and take your next career step with us.

Job Title: Data Migration Consultant - JD Edwards to Microsoft Dynamics 365
Ad Text:
Drive a major ERP transformation through high-quality data migration.

We’re seeking an experienced Data Migration Consultant to support the end-to-end migration from JD Edwards (JDE) to Microsoft Dynamics 365 (D365). You’ll take the lead on planning, executing, and validating master data migration activities, with a strong focus on accuracy, governance, and Product Information Management (PIM).
This is a key role within a large-scale transformation program, working closely with business and technical teams to ensure a smooth and successful transition to D365.

What you’ll do Data Migration Planning & Execution
Lead the extraction, transformation, and loading (ETL) of master data from JDE to D365, ensuring precision and consistency.
Develop and maintain detailed migration plans, mapping documents, and transformation logic for Customer, Vendor, and Item Master data.
Identify, analyse, and resolve data quality issues prior to migration.
Product Information Management (PIM) Focus
Ensure the successful migration of all PIM-related data entities, including product attributes, categories, and hierarchical relationships.
Collaborate with product teams to capture business requirements and convert PIM structures into D365-compatible formats.
Stakeholder Engagement & Validation
Work with functional owners across the business to validate migrated data for completeness and accuracy.
Coordinate and support UAT cycles, ensuring data is fully validated and ready for production use.
Environment Preparation & Execution
Execute and support data loads across DM, UAT, Training, and Production environments following best-practice migration and change control processes.
Monitor, troubleshoot, and escalate migration issues as required.
Documentation & Reporting
Maintain comprehensive documentation including data dictionaries, mapping files, migration procedures, and validation reports.
Provide regular status updates, data quality metrics, and issue logs to stakeholders and project leadership.
What you’ll bring

Strong experience delivering data migration projects, ideally involving JD Edwards to Microsoft Dynamics 365.
Solid understanding of master data domains including Customer, Vendor, Item, and Product data.
Hands-on experience with ETL processes and tools (e.g., ADF, SSIS, KingswaySoft, or similar).
Proficiency in SQL, data analysis, and transformation logic.
Strong documentation and stakeholder engagement skills.
Ability to troubleshoot data issues and work in complex, multi-environment migration cycles.
Experience supporting UAT, cutover, and go-live migration phases.
Why join us?
Be a key contributor in a major enterprise ERP transformation.

We are seeking a highly capable Technical Business Analyst to join our client's PMO team on an inital 6-month contract in Melbounre. This role sits within a project delivery environment and is focused on strengthening the PMO’s data, reporting, and analytics foundations. You will help redesign how project data is captured, structured, integrated, and reported—ultimately enabling the PMO to operate with greater insight, consistency, and reliability.

This position blends business analysis, data modelling, Power BI development, and stakeholder engagement. You’ll work closely with PMO leaders, technical teams, and internal capability owners to uplift the organisation’s reporting maturity and leave behind sustainable processes and internal capability.

Key Responsibilities:
Data Analysis & Modelling
Analyse existing PMO data structures, data capture processes, and reporting flows.
Design improved data models to support project, schedule, ERP, safety, and operational reporting needs.
Define data requirements, lineage, and flow across systems to create a more integrated and reliable data environment.
Data Flow & Integration Improvements
Assess current data ingestion and transformation pipelines, identifying gaps and opportunities for optimisation.
Support improvements in how data is sourced from systems such as ERP platforms, scheduling tools, and safety repositories.
Contribute to building a consolidated and governed “common data pool” to support scalable reporting and analytics.
Reporting & Power BI Development
Build and enhance Power BI dashboards and reports for PMO stakeholders.
Develop reusable semantic models and reporting datasets that improve consistency and reduce manual effort.
Work with subject-matter experts to ensure reporting reflects business logic and operational realities.
Business Analysis & Requirements Gathering
Facilitate workshops and interviews to capture reporting needs, data pain points, and system dependencies.
Translate business requirements into technical specifications for data structures, dashboards, and data flows.
Document current-state and future-state processes, data definitions, and reporting standards.
Capability Uplift & Knowledge Transfer
Coach and upskill PMO and internal teams so they can maintain and extend the data/reporting environment after the secondment.
Develop clear documentation, templates, and guidelines to support ongoing use and governance.
Ensure solutions delivered during the secondment are sustainable and aligned with internal capability levels.
Skills & Experience Required:

Experience as a Technical Business Analyst, Data-focused BA, or similar hybrid role.
Strong understanding of PMO or project delivery environments, including reporting cycles and governance.
Hands-on experience building Power BI reports, models, and datasets.
Practical experience with data modelling, data flows, and improving data capture foundations.
Ability to engage effectively with technical teams, PMO stakeholders, and subject-matter experts.
Strong communication skills for workshops, requirements gathering, and presenting insights.
Bonus points for
Experience with ERP data structures or project scheduling systems.
Familiarity with data pipelines, integration patterns, or ETL/ELT concepts.
Experience developing common data models or centralised reporting data stores.

$850 - $950 p/d .
Inital 6-month contract.
Highly flexible/ hybrid work environemnt (2 days p/w in office).
Melbourne SE suburbs location.

Pipe Management Australia (PMA) is a specialist Utilities Maintenance Company that has been operating for over 15 years and offers a variety of core industrial services. We proudly boast a modern fleet and pride ourselves in supplying experienced, highly skilled Operators to meet our client needs. We are the go-to for municipal councils and major contractors Australia wide. We operate across multiple locations throughout New South Wales and Queensland.

We are passionate about living our values and ensure that these guide us when making decisions and providing service. We know our people are what makes us great, and we want you to help us to continue making Pipe Management Australia a fantastic place to work!

Our values are Teamwork | Service | Safety | Respect.

The Opportunity

We’re looking for a highly capable, hands-on specialist to lead the integration, improvement, and optimisation of PMA’s business systems with a strong focus on Kynection, workflow design, reporting frameworks, and data accuracy. This is not a people management role. This is a senior, implementation role for someone who enjoys solving problems, whilst building real solutions that will make business sense.

You will work directly with the founding Directors, have autonomy to design and implement improvements, and play a key role in PMA’s operational and digital transformation.

In this well-rounded role, you will develop and deliver integration plans across the business including

• Lead the review, integration, and optimisation of PMA’s business systems (primarily Kynection).

• Analyse and refine workflows across Operations, Reporting, and Finance to ensure accuracy, consistency, and ease of use.

• Build, test, and implement process improvements and automation.

• Develop and maintain PMA’s reporting and business intelligence frameworks, including hands-on dashboard development in Power BI.

• Present clear recommendations, business cases, and options for system or workflow improvements.

• Oversee the rollout of approved changes to ensure smooth adoption and measurable business outcomes.

• Engage directly with Frontline Teams and Managers to understand real-world system usage and user challenges.

• Travel between NSW and QLD as required to support discovery and implementation activities.

About You

You’re a systems-focused professional with strong technical capability and the confidence to take ownership of complex workflows and reporting needs. You enjoy being hands-on and working directly with all employees with both Directors and frontline operators.

You will bring:

• Experience improving or integrating business systems (Kynection, simPRO, MYOB, Upvise, Pronto, or similar).

• Strong ability to break down workflows, map AS-IS processes, and design improved future-state processes.

• Hands-on capability with Power BI, including building dashboards, modelling data, connecting multiple systems, and translating operational data into actionable insights.

• Experience delivering automation, reporting improvements, or workflow simplification.

• Strong communication skills, able to engage Senior Leaders, Supervisors, and Field Teams.

• Solid analytical skills with the ability to turn operational problems into system solutions.

• Willingness to travel between NSW and QLD for discovery, training, and implementation work.

Experience in utilities, maintenance, construction, or service-based industries is highly regarded, but not essential. This role can be based from Ingleburn (NSW) or Stapylton (QLD) or Maroochydore (QLD).

Why PMA?

• A senior role with real autonomy, work with Senior Leaders including founding Directors

• Own the systems, the improvements, and the outcomes

• Flexibility to travel as needed and work independently

• Hands-on position in a business that wants practical results, not layers of complexity

• Major role in a genuine business transformation program

• Supportive team and strong operational culture

INTERESTED

If this sounds like you, we would love to have you join our team. Training and upskilling are available within a work environment focused on engagement, positivity and continuous improvement. Please share your details without delay to apply.
